The paper focuses on the formulation of a string buffer overflow analysis for C programs, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the feasibility of describing the analysis in terms of lattice valued functions and relations, which is a topic related to formal methods (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the construction of automatic analyzers, which is a topic related to logic in computer science (cs.LO).
